records.addlTxt:
Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalty.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Plea questionnaire received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.   

Statements made as to sentencing.  
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 4 YEARS, with credit for 16 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 2 YEARS.  The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 3 YEARS with the following conditions:  
1) Serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction; STRAIGHT TIME; 
2) Obtain AODA assessment and follow-up treatment; form signed and filed;
3) Maintain absolute sobriety with random urine screens; 
4) Pay a fine of $2400.00 PLUS all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment; out of up to 25% of prison wages;
5) Pay the IID surcharge or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment;
6) Pay the fine of $1200.00 PLUS all costs and surcharges and the IID surcharge in case 14CM004616 or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment; out of up to 25% of prison wages;
7) Pay the IID surcharge in case 14CM004616 or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment;
8) Provide a DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.



Court ordered the defendant driving privileges revoked for 36 months.  Court orderered any vehicle owned/operated by the defendant to be equipped with the Ignition Interlock Device for 36 months.  

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm.  Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. 

